Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a pottery transport amphora. Convex neck profile. Clay near fine, micaceous, red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil ''36' plus a letter. Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1372)
